## 2. Research: Neon Database

### 2.1 Why Neon?

| Factor | Neon | Supabase | PlanetScale | AWS RDS |
|--------|------|----------|-------------|---------|
| PostgreSQL | ✅ Native | ✅ Native | ❌ MySQL only | ✅ Native |
| Serverless | ✅ Auto-scale | Partial | ✅ | ❌ Provisioned |
| Branching | ✅ Built-in | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ |
| Cost (free tier) | Generous | Generous | Generous | None |
| Vercel Integration | ✅ Excellent | ✅ Good | ✅ Good | ❌ Manual |
| Connection Pooling | ✅ Built-in | ✅ PgBouncer | N/A | ❌ Manual |

**Decision: Neon is the approved choice** (per `docs/03-TECHNICAL-ARCHITECTURE.md`)

### 2.2 Neon Features Required

| Feature | Purpose | Priority |
|---------|---------|----------|
| **Project Creation** | Container for all databases | P0 |
| **Database Branches** | Separate QA and Production | P0 |
| **Connection Pooling** | Serverless-compatible connections | P0 |
| **Compute Auto-scaling** | Handle traffic spikes | P0 |
| **SSL/TLS** | Secure connections | P0 |
| **Backups** | Point-in-time recovery | P1 |
| **Read Replicas** | Scale reads (future) | P2 |

### 2.3 Neon Branching Strategy

| Neon Branch | Git Branch | Purpose | Auto-suspend |
|-------------|------------|---------|--------------|
| `main` | `main` | Production database | No |
| `qa` | `qa` | QA/staging database | Yes (5 min idle) |
| `dev` | `dev` | Development database | Yes (5 min idle) |

**3 Environments = 3 Database Branches**

### 2.4 Connection String Requirements

| Environment | Variable | Format |
|-------------|----------|--------|
| Production | `DATABASE_URL` | `postgres://user:pass@host/db?sslmode=require` |
| Production (pooled) | `DATABASE_URL_UNPOOLED` | For migrations only |
| QA | `DATABASE_URL` | Same format, different branch |

