## 4. Research: CI/CD Pipeline

### 4.1 GitHub Actions vs Alternatives

| Factor | GitHub Actions | CircleCI | GitLab CI | Vercel CI |
|--------|----------------|----------|-----------|-----------|
| Cost | Free (public) | Limited | Free | Free |
| GitHub Integration | ✅ Native | ✅ Good | ❌ | ✅ |
| Vercel Integration | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ Native |
| Custom Steps | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ Limited |
| Matrix Builds | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ❌ |

**Decision: GitHub Actions + Vercel** (per user confirmation)

### 4.2 CI/CD Flow

```
Developer pushes code
         │
         ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│    GitHub Actions (Quality)     │
│  • ESLint check                 │
│  • TypeScript type-check        │
│  • Unit tests (when added)      │
│  • Build validation             │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
         │
         ▼ (if checks pass)
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│    Vercel (Deployment)          │
│  • Build Next.js app            │
│  • Deploy to environment        │
│  • Generate preview URL (PR)    │
└─────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 4.3 GitHub Actions Workflow Requirements

| Trigger | Jobs | Environment |
|---------|------|-------------|
| Push to `dev` | Lint, Type-check, Test, Build | Development |
| Push to `qa` | Lint, Type-check, Test, Build | QA |
| Push to `main` | Lint, Type-check, Test, Build | Production |
| Pull Request | Lint, Type-check, Test | Preview |

### 4.3.1 Private Repo — GitHub Actions Limitations

| Limit | Value | Impact |
|-------|-------|--------|
| Free minutes/month | 2,000 | ~6-7 min per run = ~300 runs/month |
| Storage | 500MB | Artifacts, caches |
| Concurrent jobs | 20 | Not a concern |

**Optimization strategies:**
- Cache `node_modules` and `.next/cache`
- Run jobs in parallel where possible
- Skip redundant builds

### 4.4 Quality Gates (Blocking Deployment)

| Check | Tool | Failure Action |
|-------|------|----------------|
| **Linting** | ESLint | Block merge |
| **Type Check** | `tsc --noEmit` | Block merge |
| **Unit Tests** | Vitest (when configured) | Block merge |
| **Build** | `next build` | Block merge |

### 4.5 Vercel Integration

| Vercel Feature | Configuration |
|----------------|---------------|
| **Production Branch** | `main` → Production deployment |
| **QA Branch** | `qa` → QA deployment |
| **Dev Branch** | `dev` → Development deployment |
| **Preview Branches** | All PRs → Preview deployments |
| **Build Command** | `pnpm build` |
| **Output Directory** | `.next` |
| **Node Version** | 20.x |

**3 Environments = 3 Vercel Deployments**

| Environment | Git Branch | Vercel URL (default) | Database | S3 Bucket |
|-------------|------------|----------------------|----------|-----------|
| Development | `dev` | `nuttyfans-dev.vercel.app` | Neon `dev` | `nuttyfans-media-dev` |
| QA | `qa` | `nuttyfans-qa.vercel.app` | Neon `qa` | `nuttyfans-media-qa` |
| Production | `main` | `nuttyfans.vercel.app` | Neon `main` | `nuttyfans-media-prod` |

### 4.6 Vercel Free Plan Limitations

| Limit | Value | Mitigation |
|-------|-------|------------|
| Bandwidth | 100GB/month | Monitor usage |
| Build minutes | 6,000/month | Should be sufficient |
| Concurrent builds | 1 | Queue builds |
| Serverless execution | 100GB-hours | Monitor usage |
| Team members | 1 (Hobby) | Upgrade to Pro for team |

